The paper discusses Bayesian methods for reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on incorporating prior knowledge into learning algorithms. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), and cs.RO (Robotics), as reinforcement learning is used in these areas and Bayesian methods can be applied to improve performance.
